  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user I would like the profile editing behavior to be more consistent\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThere should not be such a big difference in terms of actions between editing from the drawer and editing from the `edit-my-profile` view.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n- touching `status` in `my-profile` view opens `edit-my-profile` view while touching `icon` and `name` does not\r\n- pressing `enter` in the drawer while editing `status` saves it and stops editing while pressing `enter` in the `edit-my-profile` view adds a newline that is deleted when adding another char or selecting the name field or image.\r\n- going through the `edit-my-profile` screen requires at least 3 taps from the drawer to start editing + confirmation by pressing the save button while editing from the drawer directly requires one tap and saves immediately when losing focus\r\n- saving in the `edit-my-profile` view just saves and doesn't go back to `my-profile` view\r\n",
